





	
                
                Parameter Tree:

                
                    EARTH SCIENCE > ATMOSPHERE > ATMOSPHERIC PRESSURE

                    

                
                Definition:

                
                    The pressure exerted by the atmosphere as a consequence of gravitational
attraction exerted upon the "column" of air lying directly above the point
in question.
                
                

                

                
                    Reference:

                    
                        
                            Glossary of Meteorology, American Meteorological Society, 2000. 
                        
                    
                    

                    

                
            


       







    
    
    
        
    

    
